message.content:
Contacting Customers

Responding to Inquiries

As a customer service representative, I will respond to customer inquiries in a timely and professional manner. I will listen attentively to their concerns, ask clarifying questions to ensure I understand their issue, and provide clear and concise answers to their questions.

Notifying Customers of Claim Investigation Results

When investigating a customer's claim, I will keep them informed of the progress and outcome of the investigation. I will notify them of any findings, and if necessary, explain the reasons for the decision. I will also provide information on any next steps or actions required to resolve the issue.

Notifying Customers of Planned Adjustments

If a planned adjustment is necessary, I will notify the customer in advance and provide them with details of the change. I will explain the reasons for the adjustment and provide information on how it will affect their account or service. I will also be available to answer any questions or concerns they may have.
